    path: /workspace/PF5-to-PF6-migration-guide.md
    content: # PatternFly 5 тЖТ PatternFly 6: Exhaustive Migration Guide

> **Source**: patternfly.org/get-started/upgrade, patternfly/pf-codemods README, PF6 release notes table
> **Current PF6 release**: 6.4.0

---

## Table of Contents

1. [Prerequisites](#1-prerequisites)
2. [Package Updates](#2-package-updates)
3. [Codemods & Tooling](#3-codemods--tooling)
4. [CSS / Design Tokens (MAJOR)](#4-css--design-tokens-major)
5. [CSS Class Name Changes](#5-css-class-name-changes)
6. [Breakpoint Changes](#6-breakpoint-changes)
7. [Component Breaking Changes (Exhaustive)](#7-component-breaking-changes-exhaustive)
8. [Charts Migration](#8-charts-migration)
9. [React Component Groups Changes](#9-react-component-groups-changes)
10. [Import Path Changes](#10-import-path-changes)
11. [Test Failures to Expect](#11-test-failures-to-expect)
12. [Manual Steps After Codemods](#12-manual-steps-after-codemods)

---

## 1. Prerequisites

- **Complete PF5 upgrade first**: Ensure your product is fully on PatternFly 5 (visit v5-archive.patternfly.org/get-started/upgrade) before attempting PF6.
- **Node.js >= 10** required for codemods.

---

## 2. Package Updates

Update all PatternFly dependencies from v5 to v6 in `package.json`:

| Package | PF5 Version | PF6 Version |
|---------|------------|------------|
| `@patternfly/react-core` | `^5.x.x` | `^6.x.x` |
| `@patternfly/react-table` | `^5.x.x` | `^6.x.x` |
| `@patternfly/react-charts` | `^7.x.x` | `^8.x.x` |
| `@patternfly/react-icons` | `^5.x.x` | `^6.x.x` |
| `@patternfly/react-tokens` | `^5.x.x` | `^6.x.x` |
| `@patternfly/react-styles` | `^5.x.x` | `^6.x.x` |
| `@patternfly/patternfly` (CSS) | `^5.x.x` | `^6.x.x` |
| `@patternfly/react-component-groups` | update to PF6-compatible version |
| `@patternfly/react-topology` | update to PF6-compatible version |
| `@patternfly/react-log-viewer` | update to PF6-compatible version |

**Victory charts** are now an **optional peer dependency**. Install separately:
```bash
npm install victory
# OR install specific packages:
npm install victory-core victory-tooltip victory-chart
```

---

## 3. Codemods & Tooling

### 3.1 Main Codemods (run FIRST, before manual changes)

```bash
# Step 1: Dry run (shows errors/warnings)
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6

# Step 2: Auto-fix
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --fix

# Step 3: Cleanup data-codemods attributes (run ONCE after all other codemods)
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --only data-codemods-cleanup --fix

# For large codebases:
NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096 npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --fix
```

**Options:**
- `--only <rules>` тАФ Run specific rules only
- `--exclude <rules>` тАФ Exclude specific rules
- `--fix` тАФ Apply auto-fixes
- `--format <format>` тАФ ESLint report format
- `--no-cache` тАФ Disable caching

### 3.2 Class Name Updater (for CSS class references)

```bash
npx @patternfly/class-name-updater <path-to-src> --v6 --fix
```
- Replaces `pf-v5` prefixes with `pf-v6`
- Simple find-and-replace тАФ may catch false positives

### 3.3 Tokens Update (for React code)

```bash
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --only tokens-update --fix
```
- Updates CSS variable references in `.js`/`.tsx` files
- Colors that can't be auto-mapped become `--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd` (hot pink) for visual identification
- Non-color globals (spacers, font sizes, box shadows) attempt auto-fix

### 3.4 CSS Variables Updater (for non-React files)

```bash
npx @patternfly/css-vars-updater <path-to-src>
```
- Updates CSS variables in `.css`, `.scss`, `.md` files
- Handles the PF5 тЖТ PF6 design token rename

---

## 4. CSS / Design Tokens (MAJOR)

**This is the single biggest change in PF6.** PatternFly 6 introduces a completely new **design token system**.

### 4.1 Token Naming Convention Change

| Aspect | PF5 | PF6 |
|--------|-----|-----|
| **Global prefix** | `--pf-v5-global--` | `--pf-t--global--` |
| **Component prefix** | `--pf-v5-c-<component>--` | `--pf-v6-c-<component>--` |
| **Class prefix** | `pf-v5-` | `pf-v6-` |

### 4.2 React Token Naming

| PF5 React Token | PF6 React Token |
|-----------------|-----------------|
| `global_FontSize_lg` | `t_global_font_size_lg` |
| `global_link_Color_hover` | `t_global_color_nonstatus_<color>_clicked` (varies) |
| `global_*` prefix | `t_global_*` prefix |

**Key**: PF6 React tokens whose value is a PatternFly token variable (prefix `--pf-t`) are now prefixed with `t_`.

### 4.3 Removed Variables

- A Google Sheets list of all removed variables is published: [Removed Variables](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vQqeH7ThYi0jkhYEB8B2SXa7x8AaY5T9ajG6o-Ogz3p7YVp0OuTulb_L3DYLDrHlY4zUE3IBiup6tkN/pubhtml?gid=1160160856&single=true)
- A list of all added variables: [Added Variables](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vQqeH7ThYi0jkhYEB8B2SXa7x8AaY5T9ajG6o-Ogz3p7YVp0OuTulb_L3DYLDrHlY4zUE3IBiup6tkN/pubhtml?gid=268831450&single=true)

### 4.4 CSS Overrides: Action Required

1. **Temporarily remove ALL CSS overrides** тАФ Many old overrides will have no effect
2. **Remove overrides completely** where possible
3. For necessary overrides, update variable names to match [PF6 design tokens](https://www.patternfly.org/tokens/all-patternfly-tokens)
4. No 1:1 mapping exists for every PF5 variable тАФ manual review required

### 4.5 Example Token Mappings

| PF5 CSS Variable | PF6 CSS Variable |
|------------------|------------------|
| `--pf-v5-global--FontSize--lg` | `--pf-t--global--font--size--lg` |
| `--pf-v5-global--spacer--md` | `--pf-t--global--spacer--md` |
| `--pf-v5-global--Color--100` | No direct equivalent тАФ use semantic tokens |
| `--pf-v5-global--link--Color` | `--pf-t--global--color--link--default` (check) |

---

## 5. CSS Class Name Changes

All CSS classes change from `pf-v5-` prefix to `pf-v6-` prefix:

| PF5 | PF6 |
|-----|-----|
| `pf-v5-c-button` | `pf-v6-c-button` |
| `pf-v5-c-page` | `pf-v6-c-page` |
| `pf-v5-l-flex` | `pf-v6-l-flex` |
| `pf-v5-u-*` (utilities) | `pf-v6-u-*` |
| `pf-v5-m-*` (modifiers) | `pf-v6-m-*` (note: some modifiers unchanged) |

The `class-name-updater` codemod handles this automatically.

### Specific CSS Class Renames

| PF5 CSS | PF6 CSS | Notes |
|---------|---------|-------|
| `--pf-v5-c-slider__step--Left` | `--pf-v6-c-slider__step--InsetInlineStart` | Logical direction |
| `--pf-v5-c-table__sticky-cell--Left` | `--pf-v6-c-table__sticky-cell--InsetInlineStart` | Logical direction |
| `--pf-v5-c-table__sticky-cell--Right` | `--pf-v6-c-table__sticky-cell--InsetInlineEnd` | Logical direction |

---

## 6. Breakpoint Changes

PF6 uses **rem units** instead of pixels for breakpoints:

| Breakpoint | Token | PF5 (px) | PF6 (rem) |
|-----------|-------|----------|-----------|
| `xs` | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xs` | `0px` | `0rem` |
| `sm` | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--sm` | `576px` | `36rem` |
| `md` | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--md` | `768px` | `48rem` |
| `lg` | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--lg` | `992px` | `62rem` |
| `xl` | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xl` | `1200px` | `75rem` |
| `2xl` | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--2xl` | `1450px` | `90.625rem` |

**Action**: Update any pixel-based breakpoint logic in your code. Divide px value by 16 to get rem equivalent.

