<!-- ============================== 6. DETAILED ANALYSIS ============================== -->
<h2 id="detailed">ЁЯФН Detailed Analysis</h2>

<!-- Package Upgrades -->
<details>
  <summary>ЁЯУж Package Upgrades</summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h3>What changed in PF6</h3>
    <p>All <code>@patternfly/*</code> packages must be updated to v6. Victory becomes an optional peer dependency. Charts move to <code>/victory</code> subpath.</p>

    <h3>Base branch (main)</h3>
    <p>Already has PF6 packages at 6.4.0. However, React is still at 17.x, <code>@testing-library/react</code> at 12.x, and <code>@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk</code> at 1.8.0.</p>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Area</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td>package.json changes</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">None</span> тАФ no package.json diff at all</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Yes</span> тАФ React 17тЖТ18, testing-library 12тЖТ16, react-dnd 15тЖТ16, console SDK 1.8тЖТ4.21, victory peer deps added</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>shared/package.json</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">None</span></td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Yes</span> тАФ added victory sub-packages, echarts, console SDK, react 18</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>yarn.lock</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">None</span></td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Yes</span> тАФ +988 / -206 lines</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>webpack config</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">None</span></td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Yes</span> тАФ <code>validateSharedModules: false</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>jest config</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">None</span></td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Yes</span> тАФ added react-dnd to transform ignore</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <div class="highlight-box orange">
      <strong>Note:</strong> The React 17тЖТ18 upgrade in goose is <em>beyond strict PF6 scope</em>, but PF6 officially supports React 18 and some PF6 features benefit from it. The testing library upgrade is directly related тАФ <code>@testing-library/react</code> v16 requires React 18. This is a gray area: partly justified, partly scope creep.
    </div>

    <p><strong>Winner:</strong> <span class="badge badge-green">semver/goose</span> тАФ While PF packages were already at v6 on main, goose addressed related ecosystem alignment (victory peer deps, testing infrastructure, console SDK). Codemods did nothing.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Modal Migration -->
<details>
  <summary>ЁЯкЯ Modal Migration (deprecated тЖТ new PF6 API) тАФ <span class="badge badge-green">CRITICAL</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h3>What changed in PF6</h3>
    <p>The old <code>Modal</code> component (with <code>title</code>, <code>actions</code>, <code>description</code> props) was deprecated. The new Modal from <code>/next</code> was promoted to main export. New API uses composable <code>&lt;ModalHeader&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;ModalBody&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;ModalFooter&gt;</code> children.</p>

    <h3>Before (PF5 deprecated Modal)</h3>
    <pre><code>import { Modal, ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated';
&lt;Modal title="Title" actions={[...]} description="..."&gt;
  {body content}
&lt;/Modal&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>After (PF6 new Modal)</h3>
    <pre><code>import { Modal, ModalVariant, ModalHeader, ModalBody, ModalFooter } from '@patternfly/react-core';
&lt;Modal isOpen onClose={...}&gt;
  &lt;ModalHeader title="Title" /&gt;
  &lt;ModalBody&gt;{body content}&lt;/ModalBody&gt;
  &lt;ModalFooter&gt;{actions}&lt;/ModalFooter&gt;
&lt;/Modal&gt;</code></pre>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>main (baseline)</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Deprecated Modal imports</td>
        <td>63</td>
        <td style="color:var(--red)">65 (+2 тмЖя╕П)</td>
        <td style="color:var(--green)">36 (тИТ27 тмЗя╕П)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>New Modal imports (from react-core)</td>
        <td>34</td>
        <td>34 (unchanged)</td>
        <td style="color:var(--green)">37 (+3)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Modals migrated to new API</td>
        <td>тАФ</td>
        <td style="color:var(--red)">0 (1 moved backwards!)</td>
        <td style="color:var(--green)">~30 files</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <strong>ЁЯРЫ CRITICAL BUG in pf-codemods:</strong> The <code>CreateDRPolicyModal.tsx</code> was already using the <strong>new</strong> PF6 Modal (imported from <code>@patternfly/react-core</code>) on main. The codemods branch moved <code>Modal</code> and <code>ModalVariant</code> <strong>backwards</strong> to <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code>. This is the exact opposite of what the migration requires.
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box green">
      <strong>тЬЕ Goose correctly migrated</strong> modals using the composable <code>ModalHeader</code>/<code>ModalBody</code>/<code>ModalFooter</code> pattern. Example from <code>CreateFolderModal.tsx</code>: removed deprecated import, added new imports, restructured from <code>title=</code>/<code>actions=</code> props to composable children.
    </div>

    <p><strong>Winner:</strong> <span class="badge badge-green">semver/goose</span> тАФ Migrated ~30 modals correctly. Codemods regressed 1 modal.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- EmptyState -->
<details>
  <summary>ЁЯУн EmptyState Refactor</summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h3>What changed in PF6</h3>
    <p><code>EmptyStateHeader</code> and <code>EmptyStateIcon</code> are no longer separate components. Title goes into <code>titleText</code> prop, icon goes into <code>icon</code> prop, heading level via <code>headingLevel</code> prop on <code>&lt;EmptyState&gt;</code> directly.</p>

    <h3>Before (PF5)</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;EmptyState variant="lg"&gt;
  &lt;EmptyStateIcon icon={PlusCircleIcon} /&gt;
  &lt;Title headingLevel="h4"&gt;Title&lt;/Title&gt;
  &lt;EmptyStateBody&gt;...&lt;/EmptyStateBody&gt;
&lt;/EmptyState&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>After (PF6)</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;EmptyState variant="lg" icon={PlusCircleIcon} headingLevel="h4" titleText="Title"&gt;
  &lt;EmptyStateBody&gt;...&lt;/EmptyStateBody&gt;
&lt;/EmptyState&gt;</code></pre>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>main</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td>EmptyState without titleText</td>
        <td>4</td>
        <td style="color:var(--orange)">1 (fixed 3)</td>
        <td style="color:var(--green)">0 (fixed all 4)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Correct PF6 pattern used</td>
        <td>тАФ</td>
        <td style="color:var(--orange)">Partially тАФ wraps <code>&lt;Title&gt;</code> inside titleText (works but non-idiomatic)</td>
        <td style="color:var(--green)">Yes тАФ uses <code>titleText={t('...')}</code>, <code>icon={Icon}</code>, <code>headingLevel="h4"</code></td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <div class="highlight-box orange">
      <strong>Codemods pattern issue:</strong> Codemods wraps <code>&lt;Title headingLevel="h4" size="lg"&gt;{text}&lt;/Title&gt;</code> inside <code>titleText={...}</code>. While this compiles, the idiomatic PF6 way is to pass a plain string/node to <code>titleText</code> and use <code>headingLevel</code> prop on <code>EmptyState</code> directly.
    </div>

    <p><strong>Winner:</strong> <span class="badge badge-green">semver/goose</span> тАФ More complete (all 4 fixed) and more idiomatic.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Button icon prop -->
<details>
  <summary>ЁЯФШ Button <code>icon</code> Prop Migration тАФ <span class="badge badge-red">BUG ALERT</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h3>What changed in PF6</h3>
    <p>Icons should be passed to the <code>icon</code> prop instead of as children for <code>variant="plain"</code> buttons. The <code>icon</code> prop expects a <strong>React element</strong> (e.g. <code>&lt;SearchIcon /&gt;</code>), not a text string.</p>

    <h3>Correct PF6 usage</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;Button variant="plain" icon={&lt;SearchIcon /&gt;} aria-label="Search" /&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>What codemods did (WRONG)</h3>
    <pre><code>// Before (main) тАФ text as children, correct for non-plain buttons
&lt;Button variant="plain" onClick={toggleShowSecret}&gt;
  {t('Switch to Secret')}
&lt;/Button&gt;

// After (codemods) тАФ text string in icon prop, INCORRECT
&lt;Button icon={t('Switch to Secret')} variant="plain" onClick={toggleShowSecret} /&gt;</code></pre>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <strong>ЁЯРЫ BUG:</strong> The codemods branch introduced <strong>5 new instances</strong> of <code>icon={t('text string')}</code>. This passes a translated text string to the <code>icon</code> prop, which expects a React icon element. These buttons will either render the text as an icon (incorrect styling) or break visually. The <code>icon</code> prop migration rule only applies to icon-only buttons, not text buttons.
    </div>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>main</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>icon={t('text')}</code> bugs</td>
