<details>
  <summary>ЁЯОп Scope Discipline Analysis</summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h3>pf-codemods: Minimal scope (but minimal value)</h3>
    <p>10 files changed, all PF-related. No unrelated changes. However, the tiny scope means almost nothing was actually migrated. A "clean" diff that doesn't fix the problem isn't valuable scope discipline тАФ it's absence of work.</p>
    <p><strong>Penalty:</strong> The diff is minimal not because of discipline, but because the branch barely did any migration work.</p>

    <h3>semver/goose: Broader scope with some creep</h3>
    <p>144 files changed. The vast majority (130+) are directly PF6 migration: modal rewrites, EmptyState fixes, CSS cleanup, test updates, dashboard cards.</p>

    <p><strong>Non-PF changes (scope creep):</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><span class="badge badge-orange">React 17тЖТ18</span> тАФ Partially justified (PF6 supports React 18, testing-library v16 requires it), but adds risk</li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-orange">@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk 1.8тЖТ4.21</span> тАФ Broader than needed</li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-orange">react-redux 7.2тЖТ9.3</span> тАФ Not required for PF6</li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-orange">react-dropzone 15тЖТ2.1</span> тАФ Version downgrade, unclear motivation</li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-orange">react-i18next 11тЖТ2.2</span> тАФ Major version downgrade, risky</li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-orange">react-helmet 6тЖТ3.3</span> тАФ Version downgrade</li>
      <li><span class="badge badge-orange">victory 37тЖТ35</span> тАФ Root package downgraded while sub-packages at 37</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="highlight-box orange">
      <strong>Scope concern:</strong> Several dependency version <em>downgrades</em> (react-dropzone, react-i18next, react-helmet, victory) are suspicious and may be errors from the AI agent. However, since the build succeeds, the actual resolved versions via yarn may differ from the specified ranges.
    </div>

    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> <span class="badge badge-purple">Tie at 8 each</span> тАФ Codemods is narrow but nearly empty. Goose has meaningful work but with some scope creep. Neither is ideal; they cancel out.</p>
  </div>
</details>

